Depends on how often it really happens.  No, I did not read the entire thread before responding.<br>
<br>
However, setting alternate experience to anything either than 0% or 100% is pretty silly.  Suppose you really thought that 30% alternate experience was worth it.  If you set it at 100% first, you'd get your skill sooner.  Then set alternate back to 0%, and level with the added benefit gained by your additional skill points.<br>
<br>
Based on my rough analysis, though, if you went for 12 points (6 basic, 6 into Fury) at level 55, you could have instead been almost 58th level.  Is it worth it?  Not sure.<br>
